The paper discusses community detection algorithms in multiplex networks, which involves analyzing different types of interactions among entities. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, since the focus is on network analysis and clustering, we can eliminate cs.SE and rank the remaining categories based on relevance and frequency of related papers. Therefore, we suggest cs.SI as the most likely category, followed by cs.SD (systems and control), cs.SY (machine learning), cs.LG (data structures and algorithms), and cs.DS (software engineering).
